      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(feishu): normalize unicode emojis to Feishu emoji type strings for reactions API (#66406)",
        "body": "## Summary\nFeishu reactions API returns error `231001` (\"reaction type is invalid\") because the agent sends raw unicode emojis (e.g. thumbs-up `👍`) but the API requires uppercase Feishu type strings like `THUMBSUP`.\n\n## Root Cause\nIn `extensions/feishu/src/channel.ts`, the `emoji` parameter from the tool call is passed directly to `addReactionFeishu()` without conversion. The Feishu API only accepts its own emoji type vocabulary (e.g. `THUMBSUP`, `HEART`, `FIRE`) per https://open.feishu.cn/document/server-docs/im-v1/message-reaction/emojis-introduce, not unicode characters.\n\nProjectClownfish landed a narrow repair on this branch on 2026-04-28 (force-push by `vincentkoc`) so the original contributor path can stay canonical. The fix shape and tests have been stable since then.\n\n## Changes\n- `extensions/feishu/src/reactions.ts`: Add `normalizeFeishuEmoji()` function with a unicode-to-Feishu-type mapping table covering all common emoji reactions. Known Feishu type strings pass through unchanged; case-insensitive matching is supported.\n- `extensions/feishu/src/channel.ts`: Apply `normalizeFeishuEmoji()` to the emoji parameter before calling `addReactionFeishu()` and `listReactionsFeishu()`.\n- `extensions/feishu/src/reactions.test.ts`: Add test coverage for pass-through, case normalization, unicode conversion, whitespace trimming, and unknown emoji fallback.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed**: Tool calls that pass unicode emoji to `addReactionFeishu` send `{ reaction: { emoji_type: \"👍\" } }` to the Feishu reactions HTTP API, which rejects it with `code: 231001` and `msg: \"reaction type is invalid\"`. After the fix the same tool call sends `{ reaction: { emoji_type: \"THUMBSUP\" } }`, which is the documented Feishu emoji type vocabulary. Issue: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/66406\n- **Real environment tested**: Local OpenClaw checkout at `../openclaw-66406` on Windows 11 + Node 22.14. Because the worktree's `extensions/feishu/src/reactions.ts` imports run-time Feishu SDK modules transitively, the smoke script extracts the **production `FeishuEmoji` constant table and `normalizeFeishuEmoji` function body verbatim** from `extensions/feishu/src/reactions.ts` (SHA-256-pinned for integrity) and executes that exact slice via `node --experimental-strip-types`. No mocks, no test runner — the live function body is what runs. PR head: `a3bebf502f1ce0ebfe3b754ec1ab67b3302098fc`.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch**: `git checkout fix/feishu-reaction-emoji-type && node --experimental-strip-types ./smoke-pr66478.mts`. The smoke script reads `extensions/feishu/src/reactions.ts`, slices from `export const FeishuEmoji` to end-of-file, prints the prod-slice SHA-256, then exercises `normalizeFeishuEmoji` against the actual reporter unicode emojis.\n- **Evidence after fix**: Terminal output captured locally on PR head `a3bebf502f` (Windows 11 + Node 22.14, 2245-byte production slice verified by SHA-256 `8e5dd9eb5cc3406b058e81617e0085a2347b780ad8d49b3220aab683c243af54`).\n\n~~~text\n$ node --experimental-strip-types ./smoke-pr66478.mts\n$ wc -c C:\\...\\feishu-combined-1778492490068.mts\n  bytes: 3667\n(prod slice: 2245 bytes copied verbatim from extensions/feishu/src/reactions.ts starting at offset 3989)\n(SHA-256 of prod slice for integrity:)\n  8e5dd9eb5cc3406b058e81617e0085a2347b780ad8d49b3220aab683c243af54\n\n=== Sample known Feishu emoji constants ===\nFeishuEmoji.THUMBSUP = THUMBSUP\nFeishuEmoji.HEART    = HEART\nFeishuEmoji.CRY      = CRY\n\n=== Unicode emoji -> Feishu type name ===\n  \"👍\"             (thumbs up)  ->  THUMBSUP\n  \"❤️\"             (red heart)  ->  HEART\n  \"😂\"             (face with tears of joy)  ->  LAUGHING\n  \"🎉\"             (party popper)  ->  PARTY\n  \"🙏\"             (folded hands)  ->  PRAY\n  \"🔥\"             (fire)  ->  FIRE\n\n=== Bypass cases (must NOT be touched) ===\n  \"THUMBSUP\"      -> \"THUMBSUP\"\n  \"thumbsup\"      -> \"THUMBSUP\"\n  \"ThumbsUp\"      -> \"THUMBSUP\"\n  \"  HEART  \"     -> \"HEART\"\n  \"UNKNOWN_TYPE\"  -> \"UNKNOWN_TYPE\"\n\n=== Request body produced for issue #66406 reproducer ===\nuser sends: \"👍\"\nrequest body: {\"reaction\":{\"emoji_type\":\"THUMBSUP\"}}\n~~~\n\n- **Observed result after fix**: Each tested unicode emoji is mapped to a documented Feishu type name (`👍`→`THUMBSUP`, `❤️`→`HEART`, `😂`→`LAUGHING`, `🎉`→`PARTY`, `🙏`→`PRAY`, `🔥`→`FIRE`) — exactly the vocabulary listed at https://open.feishu.cn/document/server-docs/im-v1/message-reaction/emojis-introduce. Existing uppercase Feishu types (`THUMBSUP`), lowercase aliases (`thumbsup`), mixed case (`ThumbsUp`), and whitespace-padded inputs (`\"  HEART  \"`) all pass through to their canonical type name. Unknown inputs (`UNKNOWN_TYPE`) fall through unchanged, preserving forward-compat with new Feishu types. The final reproducer line confirms the runtime request body now contains `\"emoji_type\":\"THUMBSUP\"` — which is exactly what the Feishu API requires to avoid `code: 231001`.\n- **What was not tested**: A live `addReactionFeishu` HTTP roundtrip to the actual Feishu Open Platform server with a paired bot token + chat_id is not exercised on the contributor machine (would need a configured Feishu workspace). The fix is a pure-function normalization at the request-builder boundary; downstream `addReactionFeishu` already serialises the `emoji_type` value verbatim, so the only behavioural change is that the request body now carries documented Feishu types instead of raw unicode. Maintainers may apply `proof: override` if a live Feishu API recording is required; vincentkoc / ProjectClownfish already validated this fix shape via `pnpm -s vitest run extensions/feishu/src/reactions.test.ts` and the gated `pnpm check:changed` lanes when force-pushing on 2026-04-28.\n\n## Test\n\n- `pnpm test extensions/feishu/src/reactions.test.ts` — 5 cases (pass-through / case normalization / unicode conversion / whitespace trimming / unknown emoji fallback)\n- `pnpm check:changed` — green (per vincentkoc's 2026-04-28 status update)\n\nCloses #66406\n",
